  1168    36 /* ------------------------- */
  1169    37 # Round Up:
  1170    38 /* This rounds up to even locations on the volume to keep */
  1171    39 /* the location of data relatively stable during fluctuation. */
  1172    40 
  1173    41 /* NOTE: For Volume specifice settings you would have to copy these */
  1174    42 /* next two sections and use them in the SettingsYours\SettingsYours for each Volume. */
  1175    43 #
  1176    44 /* You would need a copy of these two to use in a Reset function between Volumes. */
  1177    45 /* ------------------------- */
  1178    46 # Gaps:
  1179    47 /* Your Zone Gap consumption of free space is as a percentage. */
  1180    48 /* Clearly this can not exceed 100%. Keep it under 99%. */
  1181    49 /* ------------------------- */
  1182    50 # Gap Rules:
  1183    51 # Working Free Space is times Volume Used Space percent.
  1184    52 # IE. A disk 25% full has 75% free space.
  1185    53 # The zones will use up 25% of the total free space.
  1186    54 #
  1187    55 # Set the Working Gap Size to the Zone Gap Size.
  1188    56 # Actual Gap is a multiple of Zone Volume Roundup.
  1189    57 /* ------------------------- */
